    "The GPT accuracy metric compares textual responses to a standard expected answer, ensuring a match based on semantic equivalence.",
    "For numerical responses, we allow a tolerance level of 5%, which is consistent with former works [54].",
    "However, this error margin is subject to adjustment in specific scenarios where it is inappropriate.",
    "For instance, in cases involving years or countable quantities, precision is crucial, and as such, absolute accuracy is demanded, with no error margin permitted.",
    "To enhance MLLMs' chart comprehension in real-world contexts, we consider two design improvements in both the model architecture and its training."
